                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">Entertaining, clear, and mathematically rigorous</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
                      <span>5</span>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Helpful: </span>
                      <span>22</span>
                      /
                      <span>22</span>
                      votes <span class="ItemCaption">Reviewed: </span>
                      <span>1999-08-03</span>
                    </div>
                    <span>I taught a 3-week course on cryptology to academically gifted high school students and I found this book to be the perfect source. It is very clear and actually quite entertaining to read. And yet, I was so happy to see that no good mathematics were sacrificed.<P>Each chapter ends with 20 or so exercises which are doable and really help one to gain a fuller understanding of the concepts involved.<P>I would highly recommend this book to both the lay person and the professional mathematician who are interested in an introduction to cryptology.</span>
                  
              
